# ==========================================
# PetBuddy Monorepo Environment Configuration
# ==========================================
#
# This is a template file that shows all environment variables used across the monorepo.
# Each package (backend, frontend, meta-bot) has its own .env file.
#
# DO NOT create a .env file at the root level. Instead:
# 1. Copy packages/backend/.env.example to packages/backend/.env
# 2. Copy packages/frontend/.env.example to packages/frontend/.env.local
# 3. Copy packages/meta-bot/.env.example to packages/meta-bot/.env
#
# See individual package .env.example files for detailed configuration.

# ==========================================
# BACKEND (packages/backend/.env)
# ==========================================
# Server: NODE_ENV, PORT
# Database: MONGODB_URI
# JWT: JWT_ACCESS_SECRET, JWT_REFRESH_SECRET, ACCESS_TOKEN_TTL, REFRESH_TOKEN_TTL
# Frontend: FRONTEND_URL, FRONTEND_BASE_URL, CORS_ORIGINS
# Security: BCRYPT_SALT_ROUNDS, INTERNAL_SERVICE_API_KEY
# Logging: LOG_LEVEL
# Facebook: FACEBOOK_APP_ID, FACEBOOK_APP_SECRET, FACEBOOK_GRAPH_VERSION, FACEBOOK_SCOPES
# Google: GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID, GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET, GOOGLE_REDIRECT_URI
# Meta Bot: META_BOT_BASE_URL
#
# See: packages/backend/.env.example

# ==========================================
# FRONTEND (packages/frontend/.env.local)
# ==========================================
# App: NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_NAME, NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_VERSION
# API: NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL, NEXT_PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL
# Backend: BACKEND_ORIGIN, NEXT_PUBLIC_BACKEND_ORIGIN
# Socket: NEXT_PUBLIC_SOCKET_URL
# Facebook: NEXT_PUBLIC_FACEBOOK_APP_ID
# Features: NEXT_PUBLIC_ENABLE_NEW_UI, NEXT_PUBLIC_ENABLE_AI_ASSIST
#
# See: packages/frontend/.env.example

# ==========================================
# META-BOT (packages/meta-bot/.env)
# ==========================================
# Server: NODE_ENV, META_BOT_PORT
# Database: MONGODB_URI
# Backend: BACKEND_API_URL, OUTBOUND_SERVER_URL
# Security: INTERNAL_SERVICE_API_KEY, VERIFY_TOKEN, JWT_ACCESS_SECRET, JWT_REFRESH_SECRET
# Facebook: FB_PAGE_ACCESS_TOKEN, APP_SECRET, ADMIN_PAGE_ACCESS_TOKEN, ADMIN_CHAT_ID
# Instagram: INSTA_PAGE_ACCESS_TOKEN, ADMIN_INSTAGRAM_ACCESS_TOKEN, ADMIN_INSTAGRAM_CHAT_ID
# OpenAI: OPENAI_API_KEY, CHAT_MODEL, IMAGE_MODEL
# Bot: RESPONSE_DELAY_MS, SYSTEM_INSTRUCTIONS
#
# See: packages/meta-bot/.env.example

# ==========================================
# SHARED CONFIGURATION NOTES
# ==========================================
#
# 1. SECURITY KEYS (must match across backend and meta-bot):
#    - INTERNAL_SERVICE_API_KEY (32+ chars)
#    - JWT_ACCESS_SECRET (32+ chars)
#    - JWT_REFRESH_SECRET (32+ chars)
#
# 2. DATABASE:
#    - MONGODB_URI must be the same for backend and meta-bot
#
# 3. URLS:
#    - Development:
#      * Backend runs on http://localhost:3000
#      * Frontend runs on http://localhost:5173
#      * Meta-Bot runs on http://localhost:5001
#    - Production:
#      * All services typically run on the same domain
#
# 4. GENERATE SECURE SECRETS:
#    node -e "console.log(require('crypto').randomBytes(32).toString('hex'))"
#
# ==========================================
# QUICK START
# ==========================================
#
# 1. Setup Backend:
#    cd packages/backend
#    cp .env.example .env
#    # Edit .env with your values
#
# 2. Setup Frontend:
#    cd packages/frontend
#    cp .env.example .env.local
#    # Edit .env.local with your values
#
# 3. Setup Meta-Bot (optional):
#    cd packages/meta-bot
#    cp .env.example .env
#    # Edit .env with your values
#
# For detailed configuration, see ENVIRONMENT_VARIABLES.md in each package.
